  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of 40 schools, within Heet, Haditha and Al Baghdadi, Al Anbar governorate.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the proposed project is to conduct an education in emergency project by rehabilitating 40 schools within Al Anbar province, specifically in Heet, Haditha and Al Baghdadi. The assessment identified numerous schools that needed urgent school rehabilitation and the need for a &#x201C;back to learning&#x201D; awareness campaign.

The project comprises of second line response activities by helping to improve the quality of learning for highly vulnerable girls and boys aged 3-17 by: Rehabilitating damaged or used classrooms and conducting a back to learning awareness campaign. 

In all of our project implementations, RIRP attempts to involve members of the local community (in addition to the beneficiaries), in project assessment, planning, preparation and realization. The aim is to deliver gender and culturally appropriate services taking into account the special needs of all vulnerable groups, with a strong focus on and the aim of ensuring safe and equitable access for all beneficiaries, specifically considering the most urgent needs of girls, boys and women.</narrative>
  </description>
